{section: Verse 1}
We are to[F]ssed and driven on the rest[Bb]less seas of time;[F]
Somber skies and howling tempest
Oft su[G]cceed a bright sunsh[C7]ine.
In that land[F] of perfect day[F7],
When the mist[Bb]s have rolled away,[F]
